{
  "_id": {
    "$oid": "694a1e6794f2f8e0f791834b"
  },
  "serviceName": "roles",
  "content": "<p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Roles</strong></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Overview:</strong></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Roles define the type of user profiles in the system, such as </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Admin, Staff, External, Developer, or Super Admin</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">. These roles determine access levels and permissions, and help categorize profile positions accordingly.</span></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Steps to Manage Roles:</strong></p><ol><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Admin</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> can navigate to </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Roles</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> from the menu.</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Click the </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Add</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> button to create a new role and enter details such as </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Role Name</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> (e.g., Admin, Staff, External, Developer, Super Admin) and </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Description</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> (optional)</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Existing roles can be </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">edited</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> or </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">deleted</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> as needed.</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">When assigning a profile, the system uses these roles to determine </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">access levels and permissions</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">.</span></li></ol>",
  "createdBy": {
    "$oid": "681d8d2bf3a2818d4b95c5c3"
  },
  "updatedBy": {
    "$oid": "681d8d2bf3a2818d4b95c5c3"
