{
  "_id": {
    "$oid": "694a1e8594f2f8e0f791864e"
  },
  "serviceName": "positions",
  "content": "<p><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Positions</strong></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Overview:</strong></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Positions are defined based on </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Roles</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\"> and determine the specific job function of a user profile, such as </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Admin, Supervisor, Storekeeper, Technician, Vending Controller, Salesman, Incoming Machine Checker</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">, etc. These positions control the app’s sidebar and available features according to the user’s login role.</span></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Steps to Manage Positions:</strong></p><ol><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Admin</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\"> can navigate to </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Positions</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\"> from the menu.</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Click the </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Add</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\"> button to create a new position and enter details such as </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Position Name</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\"> (e.g., Supervisor, Technician, Storekeeper) and </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Role</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\"> (Associated Role).</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">Existing positions can be </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">edited</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\"> or </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">deleted</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\"> as needed.</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">The system uses positions to </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">customize the sidebar and access permissions</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\"> based on the user’s login role.</span></li></ol>",
  "createdBy": {
    "$oid": "681d8d2bf3a2818d4b95c5c3"
  },
  "updatedBy": {
    "$oid": "681d8d2bf3a2818d4b95c5c3"
  },
