{
  "_id": {
    "$oid": "6a020f70109a2b6eb922f6a4"
  },
  "serviceName": "departments",
  "content": "<p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Overview:</strong></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Departments are defined under Companies and help organize employees, profiles, and operational structures within the system. Departments are used to categorize different business functions such as HR, Technical, Operations, Finance, Warehouse, and Administration.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">These departments help the system manage company structures, profile assignments, and organizational hierarchy efficiently.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Steps to Manage Departments:</strong></h3><ol><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Admin</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> can navigate to </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Departments</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> from the menu.</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Click the </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Add</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> button to create a new department and enter details such as: </span>Company (Associated Company), Department Name , Department Code, Is Default (Default department selection)</li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Existing department records can be </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">viewed</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">, </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">edited</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">, or </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">deleted</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> as needed.</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Admins can use the table features to: Search departments using keyword search:  Filter records, Hide or show columns, Export department records,  Duplicate department records,  Send messages to selected records</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The system uses department information to organize company structures and manage profile assignments across the application.</span></li></ol>",
  "createdBy": {
    "$oid": "681d8f64547a7047806e8204"
  },
  "updatedBy": {
    "$oid": "681d8f64547a7047806e8204"
