{
  "_id": {
    "$oid": "6a0215f6109a2b6eb922f761"
  },
  "serviceName": "sections",
  "content": "<p><strong>Overview:</strong></p><p> Sections are used to organize and categorize smaller operational or functional groups within the system. They help manage structured classifications for different workflows, teams, or business operations.</p><p>Sections allow Admins to maintain organized records with section names and descriptions for better system management and operational clarity.</p><p><br></p><h3><strong>Steps to Manage Sections:</strong></h3><ol><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Admin</strong> can navigate to <strong>Sections</strong> from the menu.</li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span>Click the <strong>Add</strong> button to create a new section and enter details such as: <strong>Section Name, </strong> <strong>Description</strong></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span>Existing section records can be <strong>viewed</strong>, <strong>edited</strong>, or <strong>deleted</strong> as needed.</li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span>Admins can use the table features to: Search sections using keyword search, Filter records, Hide or show columns, Export section records,  Duplicate section records, Copy section details, Send messages to selected records</li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span>The system uses sections to help organize operational structures and maintain better categorization across the application.</li></ol><p><br></p>",
  "createdBy": {
    "$oid": "681d8f64547a7047806e8204"
  },
  "updatedBy": {
    "$oid": "681d8f64547a7047806e8204"
  },
  "createdAt": {
    "$date": "2026-05-11T17:46:30.264Z"
  },
  "updatedAt": {
    "$date": "2026-05-11T17:46:30.264Z"
