  "serviceName": "permissionServices",
  "content": "<p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Overview:</strong></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Permissions module manages access control for different services within the system. It allows Admins to define create, read, update, delete, import, export, and seeder permissions for Roles, Positions, and Profiles.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">These permissions help control user access levels and determine which features and modules are accessible within the application.</span></p><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Steps to Manage Permissions:</strong></h3><ol><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Admin</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> can navigate to </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Permissions</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> from the menu.</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Click the </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Add</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> button to create a new permission record and enter details such as: </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Service, Create Permission, Read Permission, Update Permission, Delete Permission, Import Permission, Export Permission, Seeder Permission, Role, Position, Profile, User</strong></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Permission records are organized into separate tabs for: </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Roles, Positions, and Profiles</strong></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Existing permission records can be </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">viewed, edited,</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> or </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">deleted</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> as needed.</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Admins can use the table features to: Search permission records using keyword search, Filter records, Hide or show columns, and Group permissions based on Roles, Positions, or Profiles.</span></li><li data-list=\"ordered\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The system uses permissions to control user access, sidebar visibility, and feature availability across the application.</span></li></ol><p><br></p>",
